So Internet service equivalent to what you get in a Holiday Inn Express for *free* will cost you $15 a day.	I was really impressed with their "fibre" high speed internet connection; it's even better than at home!	I can only assume that they're trying to make up the difference by charging $15 for Internet service.	The really annoying thing about this hotel -- and the primary reason for my poor review -- is their terrible policy toward charging for wireless Internet service.	Tv choices were great - even had nfl network.	Nice big flatscreen, wifi (I think I paid), and groovy infinity pool and hot tub with a view.	Wifi Internet worked well but was expensive.